<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-670-935  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 670 935.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Dec 3 1990 v7 n47 p7(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>V-Test simulates multiple users to test interactive software.andO;(Performance Software's V-Test 2.2 performance analysis software)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Performance Software announces its V-Test 2.2 performance analysissoftware program, priced between $10,000 and $100,000 depending onCPU, which tests interactive applications on the VMS operatingsystem by simulating multiple users.andP;  V-Test users can createcomplicated tests and run them on several terminals, gauging theperformance of programs under demanding loads.andP;  It can transformfiles created with DEC/Test Manager into V-Test scripts.andP;  DEC'stest software limits testing to single users and does not employcomplex script language.andP;  V-Test 2.2 is able to simulate input andoutput, and can simulate the activities of up to 32,000 users.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Performance Software Inc. (Newbury, Massachusetts) (Productintroduction).andO;Product:   V-Test 2.2 (Performance analysis software) (Product introduction)VMS (Operating system) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionPerformance Analysis SoftwareSimulation of Computer SystemsInteractive SystemsTesting.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>V-Test simulates multiple users to test interactive softwareandM;NEWBURY, Mass.andP;  -- Performance Software next week will release version 2.2 ofV-Test, a system for testing interactive applications running on VMS.andM;V-Test version 2.2 has the ability to take session files produced withDEC/Test Manager (DTM) and convert them into V-Test scripts.andM;DTM limits testing to single users and does not include a sophisticatedscript language, said Performance Software CEO Tom Hankinson.andM;With V-Test, users can design more comprehensive tests and run them acrossmultiple terminals.andP;  V-Test can also measure the performance of applicationsunder heavy loads, he said.andM;&quot;We consider DTM to be subset of V-Test,&quot; said Lori Dreyfus, a PerformanceSoftware sales executive.andM;&quot;V-Test can simulate up to many thousands of users pounding on the softwareat the same time,&quot; Dreyfus said.andM;&quot;You can also run one session at a time and compare it to previous [tests] tosee if there's any change,&quot; she said.andM;Unlike DTM, V-Test lets users look at output coming back from V-Test and towrite it to an audit file.andP;  It also enables users to time responses while anapplication is running, according to Dreyfus.andM;&quot;DTM focuses very much on regression testing and it does a good job of that,but we feel that application testing must go well beyond that,&quot; she said.andM;V-Test can simulate input and output without actual user keyboard activity orphysical terminals, and also includes a language for creating structured andrepeatable tests.andM;Applications for system testing, regression testing, performance assessmentand acceptance testing can be simulated without the need for users to test arange of applications, company officials said.andM;&quot;You build a script with V-Test which simulates the users, and [the script]provides the input to the application.andP;  The script can be built from scratchusing our script language, or you can record an actual terminal session anduse that as the basis for a script,&quot; Dreyfus said.andM;V-Test can simulate the action of thousands of terminal operators accessing aVAX or a VAXcluster.andM;V-Test records all system activity including response time for individualrequests, and analyzes system performance.andM;&quot;You can have multiple scripts running at the same time.andP;  For instance, youcould have a session that has, say, 10 uers running a database applicationdoing data entry, five users doing E-mail, and many other users doingAll-in-1 or EDT types of activities,&quot; she said.andM;V-Test version 2.2 increases the number of users that can be simulated to32,000.andP;  The update also improves function-key handling and script recordingfor the Script Control Language components.andP;  V-Test offers other extensionsto Script Control Language, officials said.andM;V-Test version 2.2 is available now.andP;  It is priced from $10,000 to $100,000,depending on CPU.andM;Performance Software Inc. can be contacted at 28 Green St., Newbury, MA01951, (508) 462-0737.andO;</TEXT></DOC>